import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.hist(data['size'], bins=20, color='blue', alpha=0.5)
    plt.axvline(data['size'].mean(), color='red', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label=f"Mean: {data['size'].mean():0.2f}")
    plt.axvline(data['size'].median(), color='green', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label=f"Median: {data['size'].median():0.2f}")
    plt.xlabel('Size')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    plt.legend()
    plt.title('What is the distribution of sizes in the dataset?', wrap=True)
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

```
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['size'] = pd.to_numeric(data['size'], errors='coerce')
    data = data.dropna(subset=['size'])
    avg_size = data.groupby('parent')['size'].mean().reset_index()
    fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(10, 6))
    ax.bar(avg_size['parent'], avg_size['size'], color='blue')
    ax.set_xlabel('Parent Category')
    ax.set_ylabel('Average Size')
    ax.set_title('What is the average size of items in each parent category?')
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    plt.tight_layout()
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
from wordcloud import WordCloud

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data = data.dropna()
    names = data['name'].tolist()
    wordcloud = WordCloud(width = 800, height = 800, 
                background_color ='white', 
                min_font_size = 10).generate(' '.join(names))
    plt.figure(figsize = (8, 8), facecolor = None) 
    plt.imshow(wordcloud) 
    plt.axis("off") 
    plt.tight_layout(pad = 0) 
    plt.title('What is the most common name in the dataset?', wrap=True)
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
import seaborn as sns

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data = data[['parent', 'size']]
    fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(10, 6))
    sns.boxplot(x='parent', y='size', data=data, ax=ax)
    ax.set_xlabel('Parent Category')
    ax.set_ylabel('Size')
    ax.set_title('What is the distribution of sizes within each parent category?')
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```
